properties.areaDesc: San Luis Obispo County Central Coast; Santa Barbara County Central Coast
properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued January 24 at 2:37AM PST until January 26 at 3:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Large breaking waves of 10 to 13 feet with dangerous
rip currents on west to northwest facing beaches.

* WHERE...San Luis Obispo County Central Coast and Santa Barbara
County Central Coast.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 3 AM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...There is an increased risk for ocean drowning. Rip
currents can pull swimmers and surfers out to sea. Large
breaking waves can cause injury, wash people off beaches and
rocks, and capsize small boats near shore.
properties.instruction:
Remain out of the water due to dangerous surf conditions, or stay
near occupied lifeguard towers. Rock jetties can be deadly in
such conditions, stay off the rocks.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 3 AM PST SUNDAY
